<tr>
<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=azlina&Board=enchanter&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=Session&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View Azlina_Crafte (azlina) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Once you get to 34, you can try spectres in Oasis.  No, I'm not kidding.  There's a reasonable write-up at eq.castersrealm.com.  I started at 35 because I was scared.  Silly me.  My CHA is 189.<p>

Just make sure you have SoW.  Spectres are slow, but you want all the speed you can get.  I carry a multi-charge sow potion for just this reason.  <p>

I've run into a few small problems doing this, so I figure I should warn.<p>

1. I can't figure out how to kill the last one.  He's got too many hp left to nuke to death.  Maybe I just need to manage my pets better.  Or zone and let the newbies deal with him.  (That'd be evil).<p>

2. If you pull 5, the fifth one acts funny.  There appears to be a game bug here.  Sometimes he'll go off on his own direction.  Sometimes he hits me from far away.  <p>

3. If you have a group (sometimes a druid joins me for heals, sow, and to help kill the last one), keep them really far away from the action.  If a spectre turns on one of them it can ruin your ability to control the situation.  And charming the one that's been snared really sucks.<p>

4. If you only pull 1, you have to go back for more.<p>

On that last one, if HP are good (4 bubs), do /pet guard or enthrall and rest up to FM.  Then go get some more.  It's like spicey food -- after a couple bites you can't stop eating.<p>

During my charm-kiting learning phase, I died about 5 times.  But none of those times was while I was actually charm-kiting.  Instead it was losing sow while playing with a sand giant or getting flustered with that last spectre or something.<p>

Once I was lucky enough to come across two sand giants that no one wanted.  Charmed one on the other, looted 34pp all for me.  And managed to avoid Cazel the whole time.<p>

I get better XP / loot / companionship in a good group.  But for a short session, or during odd hours, or when my friends are busy, or just to show off, charm-kiting spectres is just the ticket.<p>

stack of jasper for Rune 3:    14pp<br>
over 100 points of CHA gear:  ~1kpp<br>
10-charge SoW potion:         120pp<br>
Pulling the whole spectre island spawn, soloing all but one, and zoning with half your mana left: priceless.<p>

&lt;grin&gt;<hr>-Azlina Crafte<br>
35 Enchanter<br>
The Nameless</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
